library(ggplot2)
pf <- read.csv('pseudo_facebook.tsv', sep='\t')

qplot(x=age, y=friend_count, data=pf)

### alternate way

qplot(age,friend_count, data=pf)

What are some things that you notice right away?

Response:

ggplot Syntax

Notes: The main difference between ggplot and qplot is: ggplot needs to specify which geom and ggplot use aes wrap, ggplot come plot more complex plot use + to add one new layer its better to add one layer at one time

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) + geom_point()

summary(pf$age)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##   13.00   20.00   28.00   37.28   50.00  113.00
ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) + geom_point() + xlim(13,90)
## Warning: Removed 4906 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Overplotting

Notes: set the transport using alpha param, alpha=1/20 means use 1 point to express 20 points at the same location

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) + 
  geom_point(alpha=1/20) + 
  xlim(13,90)
## Warning: Removed 4906 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) + 
  geom_jitter(alpha=1/20) + 
  xlim(13,90)
## Warning: Removed 5182 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) + 
  geom_jitter(alpha=0.05) + 
  xlim(13,90)
## Warning: Removed 5172 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

What do you notice in the plot?

Response:

Coord_trans()

Notes:

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) + 
  geom_point(alpha=0.05, position = position_jitter(h=0)) + 
  xlim(13,90) +
  coord_trans( y="sqrt")
## Warning: Removed 5192 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Look up the documentation for coord_trans() and add a layer to the plot that transforms friend_count using the square root function. Create your plot!

age_groups <- group_by(pf, age)
pf.fc_by_age <- summarise(age_groups,
          friend_count_mean = mean(friend_count),
          friend_count_media = mean(friend_count),
          n = n())
pf.fc_by_age <- arrange(pf.fc_by_age, age)
head(pf.fc_by_age)

Conditional means alernate code, use %>% to chain functions

pf.fc_by_age <- pf %>%
  group_by(age) %>%
  summarise(friend_count_mean=mean(friend_count),
            friend_couint_median=median(friend_count),
            n=n()) %>%
  arrange(age)
